<TITLE> 'Inclusive' monetary policy unveiled </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 19 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh Bank has unveiled an "inclusive" monetary policy for the second half of the current fiscal year, to bring more of the population under banking services. The policy also aims to rein in inflation and boost private sector investment. "The main goal of the policy is to bring more people under financial services, " Atiur Rahman, governor of country's central bank, said as he presented the half-yearly policy on Tuesday at the bank's headquarters in the city. "Around 25 percent of the population is still beyond the reach of banking services. We want to attain growth through financial inclusion." It eyes 5.5-6.0 percent GDP growth, in line with this fiscal year's budget forecast, and 6.5 percent average inflation. b
